{"sections":[],"primaryContentSections":[{"declarations":[{"platforms":["macOS"],"tokens":[{"kind":"text","text":"object "},{"kind":"identifier","text":"SmartCard"}],"languages":["data"]}],"kind":"declarations"},{"items":[{"introducedVersion":"10.12.4","content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"If ","type":"text"},{"code":"false","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":", the system disables smart cards for logins, authorizations, and screen saver unlocking. It is still allowed for other functions, such as signing emails and accessing the web. A restart is required for a setting change to take effect."}]}],"name":"allowSmartCard","required":false,"type":[{"text":"boolean","kind":"text"}],"attributes":[{"kind":"default","value":"true"}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"Configures the certificate trust check and has one of the following possible values:","type":"text"}]},{"type":"unorderedList","items":[{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"codeVoice","code":"0"},{"text":": Turns off certificate trust check.","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"codeVoice","code":"1"},{"type":"text","text":": Turns on certificate trust check. A standard validity check is performed but doesn’t include additional revocation checks."}]}]},{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"codeVoice","code":"2"},{"type":"text","text":": Turns on certificate trust check. A soft revocation check is also performed. Until the certificate is explicitly rejected by CRL/OCSP, it’s considered valid. This setting means that unavailable or unreachable CRL/OCSP allow this check to succeed."}],"type":"paragraph"}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"code":"3","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":": Turns on certificate trust check. A hard revocation check is also performed. Unless CRL/OCSP explicitly says “This certificate is OK,” it’s considered invalid. This option is the most secure.","type":"text"}]}]}]}],"required":false,"introducedVersion":"10.12.4","type":[{"text":"integer","kind":"text"}],"name":"checkCertificateTrust","attributes":[{"value":"0","kind":"default"},{"kind":"allowedValues","values":["0","1","2","3"]}]},{"required":false,"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"text":"If ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"true"},{"text":", a user can only log in or authenticate with a smart card.","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Available: macOS 10.13.2+"}]}],"type":[{"text":"boolean","kind":"text"}],"attributes":[{"kind":"default","value":"false"}],"introducedVersion":"10.12.4","name":"enforceSmartCard"},{"attributes":[{"kind":"default","value":"false"}],"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"If ","type":"text"},{"code":"true","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":", a user can pair with only one smart card, although existing pairings are allowed if already set up."}]}],"required":false,"introducedVersion":"10.12.4","type":[{"text":"boolean","kind":"text"}],"name":"oneCardPerUser"},{"required":false,"introducedVersion":"10.12.4","name":"tokenRemovalAction","content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"If "},{"code":"1","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":", the system enables the screen saver when the smart card is removed."}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"Available: macOS 10.13.4+","type":"text"}]}],"attributes":[{"value":"0","kind":"default"},{"kind":"allowedValues","values":["0","1"]}],"type":[{"kind":"text","text":"integer"}]},{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"text":"If ","type":"text"},{"code":"false","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":", users don’t get the pairing dialog, although existing pairings still work."}],"type":"paragraph"}],"introducedVersion":"10.12.4","attributes":[{"value":"true","kind":"default"}],"required":false,"name":"UserPairing","type":[{"kind":"text","text":"boolean"}]}],"title":"Properties","kind